headline: ‘I Don’t Think There’s Much Left’: L.A. Fires Leave Thousands Looking for Temporary Housing
summary: Thousands of people displaced by Los Angeles fires this week face a daunting question: Where to call home for now.  Jean Robison and her two daughters have been staying with a friend who lives 40 minutes to the west, but don’t want to impose on their hospitality for too long.  Finding a longer-term rental, especially near a neighborhood devastated by fire, has proved daunting.
